-- Police Converge on Watertown House in Hunt for Bomb Suspect
-- B y   P h i l   M a t t i n g l y   a n d   A n n i e   L i n s k e y
-- 2013-04-19T23:17:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-19/police-converge-on-watertown-house-in-hunt-for-bomb-suspect.html
Police converged on a house in Watertown,  Massachusetts , in the hunt for the second suspect in the Boston Marathon bombing.  Police reinstated a warning to residents to stay inside less than an hour after it was lifted. Gunfire was heard in the area.  To contact the reporters on this story: Phil Mattingly in Washington at  pmattingly@bloomberg.net ; Annie Linskey in Boston at  alinskey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Steven Komarow at  skomarow1@bloomberg.net  